From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: =?UTF-8?q?=C3=98yvind=20Harboe?= <oyvind.harboe@zylin.com>
Date: Tue, 12 May 2026 09:00:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] fix: keep bazel_dep(bazel-orfs) non-dev for load() visibility

flow/BUILD has `load("@bazel-orfs//:openroad.bzl", "orfs_pdk")`, which
needs @bazel-orfs visible from @@orfs+ even when ORFS is consumed as
a non-root module.  Marking the bazel_dep dev-only suppresses that
visibility — only the git_override (which is implicitly root-only)
should be dev-conditional.

Signed-off-by: =?UTF-8?q?=C3=98yvind=20Harboe?= <oyvind.harboe@zylin.com>
---
 MODULE.bazel | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/MODULE.bazel b/MODULE.bazel
--- a/MODULE.bazel
+++ b/MODULE.bazel
@@ -34,5 +34,5 @@
 )
 
-bazel_dep(name = "bazel-orfs", dev_dependency = True)
+bazel_dep(name = "bazel-orfs")
 bazel_dep(name = "bazel-orfs-verilog", dev_dependency = True)
 
--
2.51.0
